I"›<p>When I was looking to deploy my this blog on AWS, I remember searching tirelessly for a tutorial that matched my needs. After reading many articles, I managed to piece together the steps and get it working.</p>

<p>You can setup a blog using a Static Site Generator like Jekyll quite seemlessly. However, deploying it on AWS and hooking up your own domain may be a little tricky. In this blog, I will show you how to deploy your site on AWS using S3, CloudFront and Route53.</p>

<p>In this tutorial, I will assume you already have a Jekyll blog and purchased a domain.</p>

